cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a learning algorithm for networked data sets using convex optimization methods. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper focuses on network models and their application to localized linear regression problems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses efficient implementations of the nLasso algorithm for big data over networks. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a learning algorithm for networked data sets, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the performance of the nLasso algorithm in learning localized linear regression models from few labeled data points, which involves information theory concepts.
